title: The Particulars of all the late bloody fight at sea on Thursday and Friday last. With a list of the losse on both sides from the beginning to the end. The horrid designe of Van Trump to murther the English. And an account of the whole fight: signified by a letter from both the generals at sea, to his Excellency the Lord Generall Cromwell June 6. 1653. Appointed to be printed by speciall order.
author: Albemarle, George Monck, Duke of, 1608-1670.
